				\begin{document}$$\begin{array}{l}P_{\mathrm{heat}} = \alpha \left( {\nu _{\mathrm{exc}}} \right)I_{\mathrm{exc}} - h\nu _{\mathrm{em}}\eta _{\mathrm{e}}BN^2\\ = \eta _{\mathrm{e}}BN^2\left( {h\nu _{\mathrm{exc}} - h\nu _{\mathrm{em}}} \right) + ANh\nu _{\mathrm{exc}} + CN^3h\nu _{\mathrm{exc}}\\ = P_{\mathrm{em}}\left( {\frac{1}{{\mathrm{QY}}}\frac{{\nu _{\mathrm{exc}}}}{{\nu _{\mathrm{em}}}} - 1} \right),\end{array}$$\end{document}where νem is the mean emission frequency and Pem = hνemηeBN2 is the corresponding emission power. If Pheat proportionally induces a temperature change, ΔT, Eq. 23 can be rewritten as24ΔT∝Pem1QYνexcνem-1.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
